# GitHub Account Routing

Before any git commit/push/remote changes, always verify account routing first.

## Required checks

- Run `git remote -v` in the target repo before push operations.
- For repos owned by `walhimer` or `walhimer-studio`, `origin` should use `git@github-walhimer:<owner>/<repo>.git`.
- For repos owned by `museumplanning`, `origin` should use `git@github-museumplanning:<owner>/<repo>.git`.
- If remote uses plain `github.com` HTTPS/SSH, flag it and suggest converting to the correct alias.

## Identity checks when auth fails

- Verify identity with `ssh -T git@github-walhimer` or `ssh -T git@github-museumplanning`.
- If identity mismatch appears, stop and fix routing before any push attempt.

## Useful local audit

- Run `/Users/markwalhimer/Documents/dev/git-remote-account-audit.sh /Users/markwalhimer/Documents/GitHub` to scan common repos.
